{
  "texts": [
    "Since Y satisfies persistence and refinability, from y ′ ∈ Y and y ⊑ y ′ we have that {x′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s y} ⊆ Y by Fact 4.2, so ζ F (y) ⊑ (F b)p Y.To show that ζ F satisfies R-forth, we use the fact from Corollary 2.31 and Proposition 4.42 that any full or principal possibility frame satisfies R⇒win from § 2.3, plus the definition of ♦ i Y from Fact 2.43:xR i y ⇒ ∀y ′ ⊑ y ∃x ′ ⊑ x ∀x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∃y ′′: x ′′ R i y ′′ and y ′ ≬ y ′′ by R⇒win ⇒ ∀Y ∈ P: if ∅ ̸ = Y ⊆ ζ F (y), then ζ F (x) ∩ {x ′ ∈ S | ∀x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∃y ′′: x ′′ R i y ′′ and ∃y ′′′ ⊑ y ′′: y ′′′ ∈ Y } ̸ = ∅ since every Y ∈ P is a downset ⇔ ∀Y ∈ F b: if ⊥ F b ̸ = Y ≤ F b ζ F (y), then ζ F (x) ∧ F b ♦ i Y ̸ = ⊥ F b by definition of (•) b and ♦ i ⇔ ζ F (x)R (F b)p i ζ F (y) by definition of (•) p. For R-back, suppose that ζ F (x)R (F b)p i Y and Z ⊑ (F b)p Y.",
    "By definition of (•) p (Definition 5.14), it follows that ζ F (x) ∧ ♦ i Z ̸ = ⊥, i.e., {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x} ∩ {x ′ ∈ S | ∀x ′′ ⊑ x ′ ∃z: x ′′ R i z and ∃z ′ ⊑ z: z ′ ∈ Z} ̸ = ∅.So there is an x ′ ⊑ s x such that for all x ′′ ⊑ x ′ there is a z such that x ′′ R i z and a z ′ ⊑ z such that z ′ ∈ Z; since x ′ ⊑ s x, there is an x ′′ ⊑ x ′ such that x ′′ ⊑ x; and since x ′′ ⊑ x ′, there is a z such that x ′′ R i z and a z ′ ⊑ z such that z ′ ∈ Z.",
    "Then since z ′ ∈ Z, it follows by (⋆) above that ζ F (z ′) ⊑ (F b)p Z.",
    "By R-rule (Corollary 2.31, Proposition 4.42), together x ′′ ⊑ x, x ′′ R i z and z ′ ⊑ z imply there is a y such that xR i y and y ≬ z ′, so there is a z ′′ with z ′′ ⊑ y and z ′′ ⊑ z ′.",
    "Thus, by R-forth, ζF (z ′′) ⊑ (F b)p ζ F (y) and ζ F (z ′′) ⊑ (F b)p ζ F (z ′), which with ζ F (z ′) ⊑ (F b)p Z implies ζ F (y) ≬ (F b)p Z."
  ]
}